# Planton.ai Documentation Guidelines

## Core Principle: Truth Over Speculation

**Never write documentation based on assumptions or speculation.** Every statement must be grounded in:
- Actual implementation
- Verified behavior
- Real examples from the codebase

When uncertain, **ask questions** rather than guessing. Inaccurate documentation is worse than no documentation.

## Heading Anchors

All headings (h1-h6) automatically generate anchor links:
- Headings become IDs: `## Install on Windows` → `#install-on-windows`
- A link icon appears on hover (left of heading)
- Clicking copies the full URL to clipboard (shows green checkmark)

**When referencing sections:**
- Use auto-generated anchors: `/docs/cli#install-on-windows`
- Do NOT use custom anchor syntax `{#custom-id}` — it renders literally

